property.name: isValid
property.shortdesc: Returns true if the object specifier resolves to valid objects.

property.name: parent
property.shortdesc: The parent of the FindChangeBlendingSetting &#40;a FindChangeTransparencySetting, FindChangeStrokeTransparencySetting, FindChangeFillTransparencySetting or FindChangeContentTransparencySetting).

property.name: blendMode
property.shortdesc: The blending mode for controlling how the base color interacts with the color of the FindChangeBlendingSetting. Can return: BlendMode enumerator or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: opacity
property.shortdesc: The fill opacity of the FindChangeBlendingSetting &#40;as a percentage). (Range: 0 to 100). Can return: Real (0 - 100) or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: knockoutGroup
property.shortdesc: If true, the FindChangeBlendingSetting is a knockout group. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: isolateBlending
property.shortdesc: If true, blending is applied only to the group. If false, blending includes all objects beneath the group. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

property.name: properties
property.shortdesc: A property that allows setting of several properties at the same time.

method.name: toSource
method.shortdesc: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the FindChangeBlendingSetting.

method.name: getElements
method.shortdesc: Resolves the object specifier, creating an array of object references.

parameter.name: handler
parameter.shortdesc: The event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.

parameter.shortdesc: The registered event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.
